race.comment: RUNRANIRUN (12) resumes for the Smith yard off two sharp trials and has a strong fresh record. She looks to have come back in terrific order and should take plenty of stopping. OUR LITTLE STAR (11) makes her stable debut and impressed winning her trial here. With a favourable draw, she's expected to be right in the mix at the business end. ORYX (2) has been prepared with quieter trials but owns a solid record at this journey. Needs some luck from the draw but is capable of featuring. STERN LOOKS (8) is progressive, having delivered at start two with a win at Wagga Riverside. He has more to offer but faces a sticky gate. SUPER ZIPPI (9) comes through a strong form race and benefits from weight relief. He's one to include in exotics and could surprise.
